t get out! And she had these kids to have to cope with, and he said some charity worker gave him a banana, and he tried eating the skin, and thought it was horrible! But anyway, they went, then, by boat to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Boston{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12480245 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
Twice the family was burnt out: in the Chelsea Fire, and then in the Salem Fire. His father was extremely Orthodox, but set up a tiny little cobbler\rquote s shop. And the older kids had to go to work. His oldest brother, who was a very nice man called 
Louis, became foreman in a shoe factory eventually. But the younger four went to school, and [my father] rapidly learned English, and he became a very good scholar, and the teacher picked him out and he won some prizes. 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
