 hawking things around. And then, eventually, he worked, wrapping parcels for the Parker Brothers, a games manufacturer, who manufactured Monopoly, actually. And Mr. Parker noticed him, but especially the under manager, a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}New England{\*\xmlclose} gentleman, Frank Ordway, particularly noticed him, and semi-adopted him \endash  they had no children \endash 
 and the first summer he spent with them, he gained 40lbs! He was actually malnourished and had semi-rickets from his childhood. But they literally fed him, and took 
care of him. Mr. Parker offered to put him through college, if he would do a business degree and come into the firm, and he said, no, he was going to be a doctor. He had decided to be a doctor, from a very young age. 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
