\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12480245\charrsid4223568 Leonore:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 There was a doctor in the little town, a German doctor, in the little town in Latvia \endash 
 the elite were German \endash  and his sister, Rosie, who he adored \endash  his oldest sister, who really had brought him up \endash  had begun to
 have bleeding from her mouth, and they took her, and they thought she had TB, and they were terrified. And he said, no, it was just she had bleeding gums. His sister seemed to be transformed by this wonderful man who told her she was okay, and so I think
 that made a huge influence on him. 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12480245 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
But a lot of this I know from - he wrote a memoir, which I helped him publish, so much of this I didn\rquote t know before. He didn\rquote t, like so many immigrants, he didn\rquote t want to talk about it, it was too painful. And they left
 at the time of some really bad pogroms, so in addition to the economic [problems], his livelihood, which was so difficult, that\rquote s why they left. So, as far as my father was \'85
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Do you think then there were secrets in the family? Were you aware of this?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12480245\charrsid4223568 Leonore:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 No, I don\rquote t think they were secrets, but they just didn\rquote 
t - the past was the past, and what was important was the future. And to him, science was the future. He rejected - he felt quite strongly that his father\rquote s Orthodoxy had, in many ways, ruined his brother and sister\rquote 
s marriages, and in some cases, their lives \endash  particularly his beloved next older sister, Mary, who he spent a lot of time with, and she was, she was married off to a really awful man. I mean, he was just a pig! He was terrible
. And the same with several of the other \endash  particularly the sisters \endash 
 but the brothers too, simply because they were Orthodox, because they were so Orthodox. So he turned against that, and he disliked rabbis, and he disliked the whole clerical establishment.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 What about Jewish culture in general, how did he feel about that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12480245\charrsid4223568 Leonore:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
Oh no, he was very much culturally loyal to Judaism, and to Jewish culture, and to particularly learning the book. He\rquote d been sent, you know, to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 cheder}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568  when he was three, like they all were \endash  like the boys were. So he really took against religion, and that scientific ethos was what we were brought up with, very very strongly.
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
