 trousers and things like that, and he got a Scholarship. And his father \endash  which we didn\rquote t know, again, which is in this memoir \endash  his fa
ther had been saving change from the cobbling, which he had in dimes and nickels and so on, and he had been putting it inside the \'85 the last. And dropping them into the stand. And when he heard that my dad wanted to go to Harvard \endash 
 they called it \'93The College\'94, there was no other, it had to be Harvard \endash  he opened it up and gave him. Anyway, that was my father\rquote s family. 
