\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12480245\charrsid4223568 Leonore:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Oh yes. He shot through {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}
Medical{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, because of the First World War. He was called up, put into the Army Medical Corps, and pushed through, and did all the training, the Internship, and was ready to do a Residency, when somebody fell out from going to the North Pole, as a ship\rquote 
s doctor, with an Admiral Perry. So he went instead, and got caught in the ice, and the ship was getting back, and he was terrified he\rquote 
d miss his Residency with Harvey Cushing, the great innovator of neuro-surgery. But he got back just in time, and he became his Resident \endash  the first Jew who Cushing ever took on. 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12480245 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
And my mother was at college. She was a graduate student. Oh no, she was just beginning to teach in a kindergarten as a teacher, had just graduated with an M.A. from Radcliffe. And the Hillel Society wanted to find a speaker, and because he\rquote 
d been to the North Pole, she went and interviewed him. And within three weeks, they were engaged! But Residents couldn\rquote t marry, so they didn\rquote t, until a year later. So that\rquote s how they met.
