Well, in the run up to it, and what was happening, my father, in particular, was, I think he, basically, was very afraid, having been through pogro
ms. So there was a feeling, you know, that we were always slightly under threat. And he had a hard time in the medical world of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}New York{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, because of his Jewishness, and we knew that.
