\endash  this was 1939/40. He had also done an operation on the son of a very very wealthy whisky, or something, baron, and the fee had enabled them to build a summerhouse just across the border, in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}New York{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}State{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. So they knew the area, and they liked it very much. It was not that far from the sea. And my mother always wanted to live in the country and have a garden. So they built this house in 1941. We moved in just as {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}America{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} entered the War.
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 So do you remember {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}New York{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, as a child?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
