Oh yes. Yes, I do. It made a big impression on me, this very urban landscape. We lived on the sixth floor, the flat was on the sixth floor, and if you went up on the roof, you could see the Statue of Liberty from there, across the river.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 And how far were you able to get around and see the different areas of the city?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12480245\charrsid4223568 Leonore:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Oh, we weren\rquote 
t allowed - I was only six, seven, and we were allowed to walk to the bottom of the street, w
here there was a big candy shop. My sister and I used to look in the window. But we were taken to the park, and the Brooklyn Library was just opened then, and the Brooklyn Botanical Gardens. So there was this split life between these wonderful wild countr
yside in the summer, and the flat in the winter, so that urban/rural [contrast] I was quite aware of.
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
