Oh, my brother became a doctor. My eldest sister married a doctor, who she later divorced, and then married another doctor \endash  a physician, actually. They were both academic physicians, they were not practising. My brother went to 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Medical{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and he became an academic physician, and eventually ended up as editor of }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 The Annals of Internal Medicine?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568  For the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}
American{\*\xmlclose} {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}College{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} of Physicians, he worked for them. And my younge
r sister, after having children and so on, she has just retired as Educational Director of a small museum in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}Pennsylvania{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. She married a behavioural psychologist. So it remained a heavily medical/scientific milieu \endash  very heavy.
