t go anyw
here, especially in the summers, she created a series of puppet shows, one after the other, summer after summer, which we gave in the local library, and she made the marionettes and she wrote the scripts, and we all were dragooned into doing these. And it
 was quite professional, the way she did it. She regrets, now, that she didn\rquote t go on to become a stage designer or something, but she went into medicine because of my father.
