\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12480245\charrsid4223568 Leonore:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
Yeah. She, very early, saw what was coming, and she started a programme for older women, and all sorts of things, and founded something called \'93Woman\rquote s Place\'94 in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}
Connecticut{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Did she not have those ideas from her earlier education, then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12480245\charrsid4223568 Leonore:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
Looking back on it, she did point out her teachers were, all of them were spinsters. She went to something called the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceName}}Dorchester{\*\xmlclose} 
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname PlaceType}}High School{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, I think, and many of them had Ph.D.s. These were women who couldn\rquote 
t get jobs in universities, but they taught high school, and they were wonderful teachers. They were all what she called, \'93Boston Brahmins\'94. 
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12480245 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
