\lquote 50s. I think my generation of women were particularly - it was particularly difficult in the late forties and the fifties. I think my older sister suffered a lot from that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 That you were expected to choose between being intelligent and attractive? 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12480245\charrsid4223568 Leonore:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Well
, my sister was very overweight, and had bands on her teeth, and was extremely bright. And also, the boys of her class had gone off to war, and there were practically no boys. So she took that route of being the brain, and she wasn\rquote 
t interested in sport in any way, or dancing or anything. And I was supposed to be the Prom Queen.
\par 
