, and my mother sort of adopted them, and, of course, they were a huge help. And one of them, in particular, was an Irish Nationalist, and on Sunday mornings, she used to play this Irish Nationalist programme, and they would sing Irish songs and so on. An
d I thought that kind of radicalism was very attractive. The underdog. So that, yes, that was, in a way, sub-political.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
