Because, after they moved, my father stayed in the City three nights a week, that\rquote s the way they handled that, so he 
could go to meetings and read, and he wrote a lot, he published a lot of papers and books on his subject. So she was alone, and she and I became quite close, and we talked about these things. I was pretty convinced by the age of about 15 or 16, that I wou
ld have a paid job, I could see that not being in the paid workforce, or having a profession, what it had done to her, and I was very encouraging of her to do something to go ahead.
