He was very tweedy! I thought he was terribly professorial and `waspy' and tweedy, with a pipe, you know! He was very nice to me, but the thing I remember about that interview, my mother convinced me to wear an outfit that she had made, that was, in parts
, embroidered across the chest (LAUGHS), and a great frilly collar! Something suitable for a 12-year old! It was just awful! (LAUGHS) But, anyway, I got admitted.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 And for the Greenbelt Study, would the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}
