country-region}}England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
, just after the Labour Government, was the white hope of Socialism. And things were getting really unpleasant in the States, if you were politically aware at all, with McCarthy and the crackdown on everything, and the whole Civil Rights issue 
beginning to bubble underneath and so on. There was nothing else. My room-mate and I read Simone de Beauvoir in our last year, but it didn\rquote t - we thought it was just very European and didn\rquote t have any real influence on us, any meaning for us.

\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
