\i\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Modern Woman and her Discontents}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 , by some very hard-line psychoanalyst - not Helena Deutsch\'85 and that was very depressing, actually. So we just didn
\rquote t want to know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 So you saw things in terms of sort of class conflict, with that kind of perspective? 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12662489\charrsid4223568 Leonore:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 And, of course, being in the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
country-region}}United States{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, ethnic and race. I mean, you can\rquote t avoid that. And there were discussions in the co-op and so on, and in Obe
rlin, everything had been so open, so opposed to that kind of thing. So it was not class in the sense which an English person would view class, but it was certainly power and inequality, but not gender. That did not come into it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 And race, I\rquote m wonde
ring whether you were specifically interested, beyond the Jewishness, in race issues and black people and so on, or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12662489\charrsid4223568 Leonore:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 It was in the periphery. I read - he\rquote s just died rec
ently, the famous black [author] - Ralph Ellison, I read some of that literature. And we listened to music, `Strange Fruit', and the songs and Leadbelly, and the folk singers, that was very important in that group, and, of course, to my sister also, the f
olk singing. So we knew what was going on. But it was all sort of just bubbling away. Nothing had really - it was a very dead period. Politically, well, we\rquote ve been called \'93The Lost Generation\'94, politically. And we were very very na\'ef
ve. I was incredibly na\'efve and protected.
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
