\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 So you decided to go to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}
England{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. And, I mean, wasn\rquote t that heartbreaking in some ways as a decision? 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12662489\charrsid4223568 Leonore:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
Well, George - and there was another young man, a physicist, and they were getting sort of awkward! (LAUGHS) Pressuring me to 
get married! (LAUGHS) And so one way of getting away from all that was to leave. And, looking back on it now, I realise that I think it was also a way of getting out from under the family. I had been accepted at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Columbia{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, I was not accepted to do graduate work at Radcliffe. I wasn\rquote t burning to do graduate work, but I didn\rquote 
t know what else to do. And my father had this brilliant idea that I would be able to live in the flat that he had attached to his office in the centre of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname State}}New York{\*\xmlclose}, of {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Manhattan{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, and I freaked! The last thing in the world that I wanted was to get into that world! So this was a way of getting away from my sister and all that.
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12662489 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
Just one thing very quickly and then we should finish. In my first year at Oberlin, I had a n
ew English master. We all had to take an English composition course, and about two weeks into the course, he assigned us to write something about our childhood or something, and so I wrote this and handed it in. And he came up to me, and he said, \'93
Are you Helen Davidoff\rquote s sister?\'94 It turned out he had been at Radcliffe, at Harvard before, and teaching the Radcliffe girls \'85
