raduate students. You went to see your Supervisor maybe every six weeks longer than that, only when you had something to show them, really. He would read a chapter, and he would make one or two comments, maybe one or two suggestions, and that was it. Comp
ared to what, you know, has developed now, you got very little instruction. But in a way, of course, although you floundered, and I lost a lot of time, you could follow your own route.
