\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 A
nd I usually ask people just an overview question at the end, which is, what do you think were the worst and the best things in your life, altogether?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1723874\charrsid4223568 Leonore:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Well, I don\rquote t know if you\rquote re meant to say it was the worst, but it certainly was a formative ex
perience that, as you probably know, the week that I started the job in \rquote 75, having gotten it, Harold broke his neck. He was 12, my youngest. And we didn\rquote 
t know what the outcome would be, [in hospital 17 miles away,] always at a distance, and that was just so traumatic, that whole business. And then my parents came over to help me when David was in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}India{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} for a couple of months, during the time just after he\rquote d got out of hospital, but was still in a cast. And then my father died the night 
they took the cast off, the day before Christmas, Christmas Eve. And it was enough of a struggle with trying to be an academic, because I was terribly out of practice, and that was to put it mildly. But all that happening on top of it, was just - (SIGHS) 
- that was an event, and it certainly was the worst.
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 And the best thing?
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid1723874\charrsid4223568 Leonore:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 The best thing was the Women\rquote 
s Movement, really, because all the unease and my fascination with this area between famil
y and work, or public and private and so on, finally began to make sense of things. And also it was very exciting to be a little bit part of that, even if it was very much a library, academic part of it. I always knew that I was not an activist, but I did
 march in one abortion parade in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}London{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, I actually got out there and marched, though I\rquote 
m not an activist by nature. So that it was a great privilege to enter this way. But it was also intellectually very exciting. No, I\rquote ve been incredibly lucky.
\par 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\s20\qj \fi-1871\li1871\ri0\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin1871\itap0\pararsid12846783 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Paul:\tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12846783\charrsid4223568 Great. Well, thank you very much.
